James de Villiers, News24 Durban &ndash; The KwaZulu-Natal SACP on Tuesday called on president Jacob Zuma to fire social development minister Bathabile Dlamini.&nbsp;&ldquo;No amount of defence can eclipse the devastating effects with which she and her Sassa Officials had plunge the country into the cusp of social malaise,&rdquo; the SACP provincial executive committee (PEC) said in a statement.&nbsp;&ldquo;Society must also put pressure by all means for the Minister to fall by her sword.&rdquo;The PEC said the minister and Sassa&nbsp;plunged the country onto the edge of &ldquo;social chaos.&rdquo;&nbsp;&ldquo;This human made scandal is the second worst saga since 1994, after the Arms Deal scandal,&rdquo; the PEC said.&nbsp;&ldquo;The Minister has chosen to run presidential political campaigns as its face instead of appearing in Parliament several times for wise counsel in ameliorating what was a looming crisis.&rdquo;The committee also expressed concern over the state of state-owed entities.&nbsp;&ldquo;Never before since 1994 ANC government had our state-owned entities been unstable in such great proportions,&rdquo; the statement reads.&nbsp;&ldquo;The failure of governance is finding more expression in our state utilities including proxy turf political wars.&rdquo;&ldquo;SARS, Prasa, SABC and SAA are a manifestation of this toxic state of decay.&rdquo;The committee also said the willing-buyer, willing-seller policy of land reform is not sustainable.&nbsp; We support the proposal for a land reform referendum on the policy proposal for the expropriation of land without compensation, the committee said.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.